faq:
  - q: "What is hot yoga?"
    a: "Hot yoga is yoga practiced in a heated room (30-38°C / 86-100°F). The heat increases blood circulation, loosens muscles and joints, and provides a deeper stretching and strengthening experience. At Hot Yoga Copenhagen, we use infrared technology that heats the body directly — not the air."
  - q: "Is hot yoga suitable for beginners?"
    a: "Yes, hot yoga is for all levels. We offer classes from gentle Yin sessions to intensive flows. Our instructors guide you safely through each class, and you can always take breaks as needed."
  - q: "What is the difference between infrared and conventional hot yoga?"
    a: "Infrared panels heat the body directly instead of the air. This provides cleaner air, deeper heat penetration into muscles and joints, reduced risk of overheating, and a more comfortable experience."
  - q: "What should I bring to hot yoga?"
    a: "Bring lightweight, breathable clothing, water bottles, and a towel. We provide yoga mats and practice towels. Premium members get towel service, mat storage, and laundry service."
